NAME
     cal2 – displays a calendar with colored holidays and weekends

SYNOPSIS
    cal [-Vh]
    cal add [-vH] [day] [month]
    cal delete [-vH] [day] [month]
    cal display [month|year|q]
    cal help

DESCRIPTION

  The cal2 utility (inspired in the cal(1)) displays a simple but colored calendar based on holidays and weekends.

  The options and subcommands are as follows:

  -V                      displays the command version

  -h | help               displays the help given for the commands and subcommands

  add <day> <month>       adds <day>/<month> to the internal list of holidays

  delete <day> <month>    deletes <day>/<month> from the internal list of holidays
  

SEE ALSO
     cal(1)

HISTORY
     A cal command appeared in Version 5 AT&T UNIX.  The ncal command appeared in FreeBSD 2.2.6.


